{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_57","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: SUGGESTIONS\n\n## Required Changes\n1. **Active-project canonical validation**: Commands that operate on the selected project still bypass `project.toml` validation in one important path.\n   - Current: [`resolve_active_project` in workspace_governance](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/mod.rs#L75) only checks that the project directory exists and that `project.toml` is present via [`validate_project_exists`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/mod.rs#L104). The run-query commands then use that ID directly in [`run.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs#L57), [`run.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs#L84), and [`run.rs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs#L134) without ever reading/parsing the project record. I reproduced this with the built binary: after corrupting `.ralph-burning/projects/alpha/project.toml`, `run status`, `run history`, and `run tail` all still exited `0` and returned data.\n   - Expected: Any command acting on the active project must validate the canonical project record and fail fast with a file-specific corruption error when `project.toml` is missing or malformed. This can be fixed in active-project resolution or a shared project-read guard, but the run-query path must not succeed when a canonical project file is corrupt.\n   - Reference: Loop 4 acceptance criterion “Corrupt or inconsistent canonical files (`project.toml`, `run.json`, `journal.ndjson`, payload/artifact indexes) fail fast with file-specific errors”; Master Prompt §11 “Project and Run Record Rules”.\n\n## Recommended Improvements\n1. Add CLI/conformance coverage for active-project corruption paths: malformed or missing `project.toml` with `project show` (no explicit ID), `run status`, `run history`, and `run tail`. The current suite covers explicit project CRUD corruption cases, but not this selected-project query path."}}
