{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_13","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' /root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/004-project-and-run-record-foundation/20260311194558-spec.md\"","aggregated_output":"---\nartifact: spec\nloop: 4\nproject: ralph-burning-rewrite\nbackend: codex(gpt-5.4-xhigh)\nrole: planner\ncreated_at: 2026-03-11T19:45:58Z\n---\n\nI’m reviewing `prompt.md`, the completed loop specs, and recent git checkpoints to determine what is already covered and what the next unimplemented slice should be. First I’ll map the current planning artifacts against the roadmap and the codebase state so I don’t re-spec completed work.\nI’ve confirmed the branch is sitting just after Loop 3 planning, with loops 1 through 3 committed in git and conformance coverage matching those slices. Next I’m reading the actual spec artifacts and the current Rust modules to check whether roadmap step 4 has already been partially built or only stubbed.\nThe loop artifacts live under the hidden `.ralph/` planning workspace, not in the Rust crate itself. I’m reading those specs plus the current source modules now to determine whether the next slice is the canonical project/run store from roadmap step 4 or whether some of that was already pulled forward.\nThe approved specs line up cleanly with roadmap slices 1 through 3. I’m now checking the current `project_run_record`, `project` CLI, and `run` CLI surfaces to see whether any slice-4 behavior already exists, so the next spec only covers the actual gap.\nSlice 4 is still empty in code: `project_run_record` is only a stub, `project create/list/show/delete` are unimplemented, and every `run` subcommand still exits `NotYetImplemented`. I’m confirming there isn’t hidden project/run persistence elsewhere and then I’ll draft the next feature around that gap.\nI’ve verified there’s no hidden implementation beyond Loop 3. To tighten the next spec, I’m pulling the architecture notes for the `project_run_record` context from the repo docs so the acceptance criteria line up with the intended storage model and invariants, not just the roadmap headline.\nThe roadmap and architecture notes both point to the same next gap: `Project & Run Record`. I’m pulling the scenario notes around project creation and durable-history-vs-runtime-log separation so the spec includes the right invariants for failure handling and query behavior.\nI have enough to choose the slice. I’m doing one last pass over the shared error types and current storage helpers so the file list and failure-mode criteria match the crate’s existing structure instead of inventing a parallel design.\n# Feature: Project and Run Record Foundation\n\n## Description\nLoops 1 through 3 are complete: the rewrite already has workspace bootstrap, built-in flow discovery, stage-contract/rendering infrastructure, and workspace governance with effective config plus active-project resolution. The next missing slice is roadmap step 4: make `project_run_record` the durable source of truth by implementing canonical project storage, initial run/journal state, project CRUD, and read-only run query commands.\n\nCurrent HEAD still has `src/contexts/project_run_record/mod.rs` as a stub, `project create/list/show/delete` unimplemented, and all `run` commands unimplemented. This feature should fill that gap without re-planning completed flow, config, or active-project work.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `ralph-burning project create --id <id> --name <name> --prompt <file> --flow <flow-id>` validates workspace version, project ID, flow preset, prompt readability, and duplicate IDs before any filesystem mutation.\n- [ ] Successful project creation writes `.ralph-burning/projects/<project-id>/project.toml`, `prompt.md`, `run.json`, `journal.ndjson`, `sessions.json`, `history/payloads/`, `history/artifacts/`, `runtime/logs/`, `runtime/backend/`, `runtime/temp/`, `amendments/`, and `rollback/`.\n- [ ] `project.toml` persists immutable project metadata: `id`, `name`, fixed `flow`, copied prompt reference, prompt hash, creation timestamp, and durable status summary. Flow cannot be changed after creation by any CLI or store path.\n- [ ] `run.json` persists canonical run state only: active run pointer, run status, optional stage cursor, cycle history, completion rounds, rollback-point metadata, amendment-queue state, and status summary. It must not infer state from artifacts or logs.\n- [ ] `journal.ndjson` is append-only, sequence-ordered, and initialized with a `project_created` event. Queries derive state from canonical run state plus journal, never from Markdown scans.\n- [ ] `sessions.json` initializes as a valid empty session store, separate from durable history.\n- [ ] `project create` is atomic. If prompt copy, snapshot write, or journal initialization fails, the new project is not visible to `project list/show`, no partial canonical files remain exposed, and `.ralph-burning/active-project` is unchanged.\n- [ ] Duplicate project creation fails non-zero with a clear error and leaves existing project state unchanged.\n- [ ] `project create` does not implicitly select the new project; active-project mutation remains the job of the already-implemented `project select`.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning project list` reads canonical project records, not raw directory names, and shows enough summary data to identify each project plus whether it is the active selection.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning project show [<id>]` shows explicit project data when `<id>` is provided and otherwise resolves the active project through workspace governance. Output includes flow, prompt hash/reference, created timestamp, run summary, and rollback summary.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning project delete <id>` deletes only projects with no active run. If the deleted project was selected, `.ralph-burning/active-project` is cleared only after the delete succeeds. If delete fails after validation, the project remains addressable and the active-project pointer is unchanged.\n- [ ] Add payload/artifact store models and enumeration APIs for durable history. If a payload write succeeds but its artifact companion write/index fails, `run history` and `run tail` must not expose a partial durable-history record.\n- [ ] Runtime logs are stored and queried separately from durable history. Runtime-log write failures must not fabricate, remove, or reorder durable history.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning run status` reads canonical state for the active project and reports either “not started” or the persisted run snapshot without inferring from artifacts.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning run history` shows durable history only: journal events plus payload/artifact records in canonical order. Runtime logs never appear there.\n- [ ] `ralph-burning run tail` shows durable history only by default, and `ralph-burning run tail --logs` appends the newest runtime logs after the durable section without changing the durable-history portion.\n- [ ] Corrupt or inconsistent canonical files (`project.toml`, `run.json`, `journal.ndjson`, payload/artifact indexes) fail fast with file-specific errors. Commands must not fall back to rendered Markdown or directory scans when canonical state is invalid.\n- [ ] Introduce `ProjectStorePort`, `JournalStorePort`, `ArtifactStorePort`, and `RuntimeLogStorePort` boundaries inside `contexts/project_run_record`, with filesystem-backed adapters using atomic writes/renames.\n- [ ] Add domain/unit tests for immutable flow, journal sequencing, and history/log separation; service tests with fake ports; adapter contract tests for filesystem round trips and corruption visibility; and CLI integration tests for project CRUD plus run queries.\n- [ ] Add public Gherkin coverage for project creation, duplicate IDs, immutable flow, list/show/delete behavior, no-active-run status, durable-history-only queries, and `run tail --logs` separation semantics.\n- [ ] `cargo test` and `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` pass.\n\n## Files to Modify/Create\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/mod.rs` - expose the context surface, core ports, and public use cases\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs` - define project records, run snapshots, journal events, payload/artifact records, runtime-log records, and rollback metadata\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs` - implement create/list/show/delete and run query use cases with invariant checks\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/queries.rs` - build canonical read models for status, history, and tail\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/journal.rs` - define append/read ordering and sequence validation for `journal.ndjson`\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs` - add atomic project staging, canonical snapshot reads/writes, NDJSON append helpers, prompt hashing, and active-project clearing on delete\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/project.rs` - replace stubs for `create`, `list`, `show`, and `delete` while preserving existing `select`\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs` - implement `status`, `history`, and `tail`; keep `start`, `resume`, and `rollback` as later-slice work\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs` - add duplicate-project, corrupt-record, invalid-prompt, active-run-delete, and journal-sequence error variants\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/project_records.feature` - public scenarios for project CRUD and immutable flow\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_queries.feature` - public scenarios for status/history/tail and runtime-log separation\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/project_run_record_test.rs` - domain and service tests for project/run invariants\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/journal_test.rs` - journal ordering, corruption, and append semantics\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/query_test.rs` - durable-history and runtime-log separation tests\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs` - CLI integration coverage for project and run query commands\n\n## Dependencies\n- Requires: Loop 1 foundation, Loop 2 stage contract registry and deterministic rendering, Loop 3 workspace governance effective config and active project resolution\n- Blocks: Agent-driven `run start` orchestration, resume/retry/rollback semantics, and requirements-to-project handoff\n\n---\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_14","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' /root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/project.rs\"","aggregated_output":"use std::path::PathBuf;\n\nuse chrono::Utc;\nuse clap::{Args, Subcommand};\n\nuse crate::adapters::fs::{\n    FsActiveProjectStore, FsJournalStore, FsProjectStore, FsRunSnapshotStore, FileSystem,\n};\nuse crate::contexts::project_run_record::model::ProjectStatusSummary;\nuse crate::contexts::project_run_record::service::{self, CreateProjectInput};\nuse crate::contexts::workspace_governance;\nuse crate::shared::domain::{FlowPreset, ProjectId};\nuse crate::shared::error::{AppError, AppResult};\n\n#[derive(Debug, Args)]\npub struct ProjectCommand {\n    #[command(subcommand)]\n    pub command: ProjectSubcommand,\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Subcommand)]\npub enum ProjectSubcommand {\n    Create(ProjectCreateArgs),\n    Select { id: String },\n    List,\n    Show { id: Option<String> },\n    Delete { id: String },\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Args)]\npub struct ProjectCreateArgs {\n    #[arg(long)]\n    pub id: String,\n    #[arg(long)]\n    pub name: String,\n    #[arg(long)]\n    pub prompt: PathBuf,\n    #[arg(long)]\n    pub flow: String,\n}\n\npub async fn handle(command: ProjectCommand) -> AppResult<()> {\n    match command.command {\n        ProjectSubcommand::Select { id } => {\n            let current_dir = std::env::current_dir()?;\n            let project_id = ProjectId::new(id)?;\n            workspace_governance::set_active_project(&current_dir, &project_id)?;\n            println!(\"Selected project {}\", project_id);\n            Ok(())\n        }\n        ProjectSubcommand::Create(args) => handle_create(args).await,\n        ProjectSubcommand::List => handle_list().await,\n        ProjectSubcommand::Show { id } => handle_show(id).await,\n        ProjectSubcommand::Delete { id } => handle_delete(id).await,\n    }\n}\n\nasync fn handle_create(args: ProjectCreateArgs) -> AppResult<()> {\n    let current_dir = std::env::current_dir()?;\n\n    // Validate workspace version\n    let config = workspace_governance::load_workspace_config(&current_dir)?;\n    workspace_governance::ensure_supported_workspace_version(&config)?;\n\n    // Validate project ID\n    let project_id = ProjectId::new(args.id)?;\n\n    // Validate flow preset\n    let flow: FlowPreset = args.flow.parse()?;\n\n    // Validate prompt file is readable\n    let prompt_path = if args.prompt.is_absolute() {\n        args.prompt.clone()\n    } else {\n        current_dir.join(&args.prompt)\n    };\n\n    let prompt_contents = std::fs::read_to_string(&prompt_path).map_err(|e| {\n        AppError::InvalidPrompt {\n            path: args.prompt.display().to_string(),\n            reason: e.to_string(),\n        }\n    })?;\n\n    if prompt_contents.trim().is_empty() {\n        return Err(AppError::InvalidPrompt {\n            path: args.prompt.display().to_string(),\n            reason: \"prompt file is empty\".to_owned(),\n        });\n    }\n\n    let prompt_hash = FileSystem::prompt_hash(&prompt_contents);\n\n    let store = FsProjectStore;\n    let journal_store = FsJournalStore;\n\n    let input = CreateProjectInput {\n        id: project_id,\n        name: args.name,\n        flow,\n        prompt_path: args.prompt.display().to_string(),\n        prompt_contents,\n        prompt_hash,\n        created_at: Utc::now(),\n    };\n\n    let record = service::create_project(&store, &journal_store, &current_dir, input)?;\n\n    println!(\n        \"Created project '{}' with flow '{}'\",\n        record.id, record.flow\n    );\n    Ok(())\n}\n\nasync fn handle_list() -> AppResult<()> {\n    let current_dir = std::env::current_dir()?;\n\n    // Validate workspace\n    let config = workspace_governance::load_workspace_config(&current_dir)?;\n    workspace_governance::ensure_supported_workspace_version(&config)?;\n\n    let store = FsProjectStore;\n    let active_store = FsActiveProjectStore;\n\n    let entries = service::list_projects(&store, &active_store, &current_dir)?;\n\n    if entries.is_empty() {\n        println!(\"No projects found.\");\n        return Ok(());\n    }\n\n    for entry in &entries {\n        let active_marker = if entry.is_active { \" *\" } else { \"\" };\n        let status = match entry.status_summary {\n            ProjectStatusSummary::Created => \"created\",\n            ProjectStatusSummary::Active => \"active\",\n            ProjectStatusSummary::Completed => \"completed\",\n            ProjectStatusSummary::Failed => \"failed\",\n        };\n        println!(\n            \"  {}{} ({}) [{}] - {}\",\n            entry.id, active_marker, entry.flow, status, entry.name\n        );\n    }\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n\nasync fn handle_show(id: Option<String>) -> AppResult<()> {\n    let current_dir = std::env::current_dir()?;\n\n    // Validate workspace\n    let config = workspace_governance::load_workspace_config(&current_dir)?;\n    workspace_governance::ensure_supported_workspace_version(&config)?;\n\n    // Resolve project ID: explicit or active project\n    let project_id = match id {\n        Some(raw) => ProjectId::new(raw)?,\n        None => workspace_governance::resolve_active_project(&current_dir)?,\n    };\n\n    let store = FsProjectStore;\n    let run_store = FsRunSnapshotStore;\n    let journal_store = FsJournalStore;\n    let active_store = FsActiveProjectStore;\n\n    let detail = service::show_project(\n        &store,\n        &run_store,\n        &journal_store,\n        &active_store,\n        &current_dir,\n        &project_id,\n    )?;\n\n    let active_label = if detail.is_active { \" (active)\" } else { \"\" };\n    println!(\"Project: {}{}\", detail.record.id, active_label);\n    println!(\"Name: {}\", detail.record.name);\n    println!(\"Flow: {}\", detail.record.flow);\n    println!(\"Prompt reference: {}\", detail.record.prompt_reference);\n    println!(\"Prompt hash: {}\", detail.record.prompt_hash);\n    println!(\"Created: {}\", detail.record.created_at);\n    println!(\"Run status: {}\", detail.run_snapshot.status_summary);\n    println!(\"Journal events: {}\", detail.journal_event_count);\n    println!(\"Rollback points: {}\", detail.rollback_count);\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n\nasync fn handle_delete(id: String) -> AppResult<()> {\n    let current_dir = std::env::current_dir()?;\n\n    // Validate workspace\n    let config = workspace_governance::load_workspace_config(&current_dir)?;\n    workspace_governance::ensure_supported_workspace_version(&config)?;\n\n    let project_id = ProjectId::new(id)?;\n\n    let store = FsProjectStore;\n    let run_store = FsRunSnapshotStore;\n    let active_store = FsActiveProjectStore;\n\n    service::delete_project(\n        &store,\n        &run_store,\n        &active_store,\n        &current_dir,\n        &project_id,\n    )?;\n\n    println!(\"Deleted project '{}'\", project_id);\n    Ok(())\n}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
