{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_16","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' /root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/004-project-and-run-record-foundation/20260311212742-impl-response-007.md\"","aggregated_output":"---\nartifact: impl-response\nloop: 4\niteration: 7\nproject: ralph-burning-rewrite\nbackend: claude(opus)\nrole: implementer\ncreated_at: 2026-03-11T21:27:42Z\n---\n\n# Implementation Response (Iteration 7)\n\n## Changes Made\n1. **Transactional `project delete` across pointer cleanup** — Replaced the single `delete_project` method on `ProjectStorePort` with a three-phase `stage_delete`/`commit_delete`/`rollback_delete` workflow. `stage_delete` atomically renames the project to `.{id}.pending-delete` (invisible to list/show but data preserved). In `service::delete_project`, if `clear_active_project` fails after staging, `rollback_delete` restores the project to its canonical path before returning the error. `commit_delete` runs best-effort after the pointer is cleared. Removed the now-unused `copy_dir_recursive` fallback.\n\n2. **Empty `journal.ndjson` fails fast as corrupt** — Added `validate_journal_integrity` to `journal.rs`, called at the end of `parse_journal`. It rejects empty journals and journals whose first event is not `project_created`, returning `CorruptRecord` with file-specific details. This makes `project show`, `run history`, and `run tail` all fail fast on truncated or malformed journals.\n\n3. **Updated test for delete-pointer semantics** — Replaced `delete_project_propagates_clear_pointer_failure_after_successful_delete` (which locked in the buggy behavior) with `delete_project_rolls_back_on_clear_pointer_failure`, verifying that `rollback_delete` is called when `clear_active_project` fails. Renamed the stage-failure test accordingly.\n\n4. **Adapter contract tests** — Replaced `project_store_delete_removes_project` with four new tests covering stage+commit, stage+rollback, and no-op edge cases. Added `journal_store_empty_file_returns_corrupt_error`.\n\n5. **CLI regression tests** — Added `empty_journal_fails_fast_on_project_show`, `empty_journal_fails_fast_on_run_history`, `empty_journal_fails_fast_on_run_tail` for journal integrity. Added `delete_with_unremovable_active_pointer_restores_project` verifying the project is restored when pointer clear fails.\n\n6. **Journal unit tests** — Changed `parse_journal_handles_empty_content` to expect error. Added `parse_journal_rejects_non_project_created_first_event`.\n\n7. **Conformance scenarios** — Updated SC-PROJ-023 for restore semantics. Added SC-RUN-024 through SC-RUN-027 for journal integrity fail-fast.\n\n## Could Not Address\nNone\n\n## Pending Changes (Pre-Commit)\n- 10 files modified\n- 207 tests passing (53 CLI + 154 unit), clippy clean\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
