{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_50","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: SUGGESTIONS\n\n## Required Changes\n1. **`run tail --logs` latest-log semantics**: narrow runtime-log output to the latest/newest runtime logs instead of concatenating every log file under `runtime/logs/`.\n   - Current: [`FsRuntimeLogStore::read_runtime_logs`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs#L507) collects all `.ndjson` files, sorts by path, and appends every parsed entry from every file. [`run_tail`](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs#L301) then returns that full set unchanged. In a black-box repro with `runtime/logs/001.ndjson` containing `old log` and `runtime/logs/002.ndjson` containing `new log`, `run tail --logs` printed both entries.\n   - Expected: `run tail --logs` should append only the latest/newest runtime logs after the durable section. If multiple runtime log files exist, older log streams should not be included by default.\n   - Reference: Loop 4 acceptance criterion “`ralph-burning run tail --logs` appends the newest runtime logs after the durable section”; `prompt.md` CLI clarification “`run tail --logs` appends latest runtime logs”.\n\n## Recommended Improvements\n1. Add CLI/conformance coverage for multiple runtime log files so the “latest/newest only” behavior is locked in and doesn’t regress."}}
